3
00:00:50,010 --> 00:01:20,000
<b>TO MY DEAR DAVID</b>

4
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:50,000
<b>DAD AND MUM LOVE YOU FOREVER!</b>

5
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:56,019
黑烟囱……冒黑烟……
Chim chiminy, Chim chiminy Chim chim cheree

6
00:01:56,269 --> 00:02:00,316
烟囱清扫工就是幸运星
A sweep is as lucky as lucky can be

7
00:02:00,566 --> 00:02:04,028
黑烟囱……冒黑烟……
Chim chiminy, Chim chiminy Chim chim cheroo

8
00:02:04,278 --> 00:02:08,450
当他和你握手的时候，幸运就会传染给你
Good luck will rub off when he shakes hands with you

9
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:12,538
黑烟囱……冒黑烟……
Chim chiminy Chim chim cheree, chim cheroo

10
00:02:12,788 --> 00:02:13,915
Rum diddly-diddly-diddly
Rum diddle-die

11
00:02:14,165 --> 00:02:17,627
Rum diddly-diddly-diddly
Rum diddle-die

12
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:25,872
女士们，先生们
All right, ladies and gents...

13
00:03:26,123 --> 00:03:28,500
这样的场合，幽默诗正好派上用场
comical poems suitable for the occasion...

14
00:03:28,751 --> 00:03:32,296
即兴创作，当场发表
extemporized and thought up before your very eyes.

15
00:03:32,547 --> 00:03:34,507
好的，我们开始
All right, here we go.

16
00:03:34,758 --> 00:03:38,512
这是我们共同的天地
Room here for everyone Gather around

17
00:03:38,762 --> 00:03:40,973
警察先生克尽职守
The constable's "responstable".

18
00:03:41,223 --> 00:03:45,145
听起来还不错吧？
Now, how does that sound?

19
00:03:48,023 --> 00:03:51,902
你好，拉克小姐 让我为你献上一首
Hello, Miss Lark I got one for you

20
00:03:52,153 --> 00:03:58,493
拉克小姐喜欢和安德鲁在公园散步
Miss Lark likes to walk in the park with Andrew.

21
00:03:58,702 --> 00:04:02,832
你好啊，安德鲁
Hello, Andrew.

22
00:04:03,249 --> 00:04:07,712
啊，考利夫人 一个关于你的故事
Ah, Mrs Cory a story for you

23
00:04:07,963 --> 00:04:10,674
你的女儿过去比你矮……
Your daughters were shorter than you...

24
00:04:10,924 --> 00:04:14,804
但现在，她们长高了
but they grew.

25
00:04:20,227 --> 00:04:24,064
亲爱的帕西蒙小姐
Dear Miss Persimmon...

26
00:04:24,231 --> 00:04:27,068
嗯？
Yes?

27
00:04:27,318 --> 00:04:29,571
风，从东方刮来
Wind's in the east

28
00:04:29,821 --> 00:04:32,616
雾，在四处弥漫
Mist comin' in.

29
00:04:32,866 --> 00:04:38,706
一件酝酿已久的事情看似就要发生
Like something is brewin' about to begin

30
00:04:39,457 --> 00:04:44,797
没人能够预测未来
Can't put me finger on what lies in store

31
00:04:45,047 --> 00:04:47,550
但我知道将要发生的一切……
But I feel what's to happen...

32
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:52,389
都曾经发生过
all happened before.

33
00:04:53,265 --> 00:04:56,936
对不起，刚才说到哪里了？
I'm sorry. Where was I?

34
00:05:20,838 --> 00:05:25,176
谢谢，谢谢你的支持
Thank you, one and all, for your kind support.

35
00:05:27,804 --> 00:05:32,435
啊，拉克小姐，谢谢。
Ah, Miss Lark, thank you.

36
00:05:32,935 --> 00:05:35,897
天主保佑你
Crikey. Bless you, guv.

37
00:05:36,147 --> 00:05:38,650
您就是慷慨的化身
Generosity itself, that's what you are.

38
00:05:38,901 --> 00:05:42,530
您就免了。
No charge.

39
00:05:43,448 --> 00:05:47,577
哦，是你啊！你好。
Oh, it's you! Hello.

40
00:05:48,245 --> 00:05:51,498
你是说，樱桃树大街17号么？
Number 17 Cherry Tree Lane, you say?

41
00:05:51,749 --> 00:05:55,336
好吧，跟我来。
All right. Come along with me.

42
00:05:55,378 --> 00:05:58,507
这就是樱桃树大街
This here's Cherry Tree Lane.

43
00:05:58,757 --> 00:06:02,136
一个很可爱的地方
Nice little spot, you might say.

44
00:06:02,386 --> 00:06:06,516
17号就在前面
Number 17's just down a bit.

45
00:06:08,810 --> 00:06:11,522
这个能给人留下深刻印象的大房子第一眼看上去并不舒服
Now, this imposing edifice what first greets the eye...

46
00:06:11,772 --> 00:06:14,191
它是退役海军上将
is the home of Admiral Boom...

47
00:06:14,442 --> 00:06:16,360
鲍默将军的家
late of His Majesty's Navy.

48
00:06:16,611 --> 00:06:18,363
他的房子就像一艘船
Likes his house shipshape, he does...

49
00:06:18,613 --> 00:06:23,577
他做事更是井井有条，一丝不苟
shipshape and bristol fashion at all times.

50
00:06:27,999 --> 00:06:31,336
报时枪准备
准备完毕，将军
Time gun ready?
Ready and charged, sir.

51
00:06:31,586 --> 00:06:34,339
还有3分零6秒
是，将军
Three minutes and six seconds.
Aye, aye, sir.

52
00:06:34,590 --> 00:06:38,511
将军一向以准时而闻名
What he's famous for is punctuality.

53
00:06:38,761 --> 00:06:40,930
全世界都以格林尼治时间为准
The whole world takes its time from Greenwich.

54
00:06:41,181 --> 00:06:44,977
但人们说格林尼治以将军的时间为准
But Greenwich, they say, takes its time from Admiral Boom.

55
00:06:45,227 --> 00:06:46,729
情况还好么，将军？
What cheer, Admiral?

56
00:06:46,979 --> 00:06:50,149
下午好，年轻人。你要到哪儿去？
Good afternoon to you, young man. Where are you bound?

57
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:53,653
17号那儿有个聚会，我想去看看
Number 17. Got some parties here in tow what wants to see it.

58
00:06:53,904 --> 00:06:56,615
把这事记入航海日志
是，将军
Enter that in the log.
Aye, aye, sir.

59
00:06:56,865 --> 00:06:58,784
应该提醒你，年轻人
A word of advice, young man:

60
00:06:59,035 --> 00:07:01,871
17号地区的暴风雨迹象已经很明显
Storm signals are up at Number 17.

61
00:07:02,121 --> 00:07:04,291
天气马上就要变坏
Bit of heavy weather brewing there.

62
00:07:04,541 --> 00:07:08,504
谢谢，我会留神的
Thank you, sir. Keep an eye skinned.

63
00:07:09,296 --> 00:07:12,550
这就是樱桃树大街17号
Here we are. Number 17 Cherry Tree Lane.

64
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:17,055
乔治?班克斯先生的住所
Residence of George Banks, Esquire.

65
00:07:17,055 --> 00:07:20,017
噢，将军的话一点都没错
Hello, hello, hello. The Admiral's right.

66
00:07:20,267 --> 00:07:24,397
17号地区的天气很恶劣
Heavy weather brewin' at Number 17, and no mistake.

67
00:07:24,647 --> 00:07:26,191
别理她！
住嘴！
Leave her alone!
Shut up!

68
00:07:26,441 --> 00:07:28,944
我告诉你，不要试图阻止这个恶人！
I'll show you. Don't you be trying to stop the wretched creature!

69
00:07:29,194 --> 00:07:31,322
让她走，我说，她走了真好！
Let her go, that's what I say, and good riddance!

70
00:07:31,572 --> 00:07:33,491
从她踏进门的那刻起，我就没喜欢过她
I never liked her from the moment she set foot in the door.

71
00:07:33,741 --> 00:07:38,372
但没有了保姆，谁来对付那两个孩子？我么？天！
But who gets stuck with the children with no nanny in the house? Me, that's who!

72
00:07:38,622 --> 00:07:40,708
瞧她那高傲的样子！
Her and her high and mighty ways!

73
00:07:40,958 --> 00:07:42,752
还有她那张脸，我已经受够了
And that face of her that would stop a coal barge, it would.

74
00:07:43,002 --> 00:07:46,172
事实上，布里夫人！你就是把全世界的财宝
Indeed, Mrs Brill! I wouldn't stay in this house another minute...

75
00:07:46,422 --> 00:07:48,925
都堆在我面前，我也不会再多呆一分钟
not if you heap me with all the jewels in Christendom.

76
00:07:49,176 --> 00:07:51,595
不，不，卡蒂保姆，别走！
No, no, Katie Nanna, don't go!

77
00:07:51,845 --> 00:07:53,013
别挡着门
Stand away from that door, my girl!

78
00:07:53,264 --> 00:07:55,683
你让我们怎么和主人说孩子的事呢？
But what am I gonna tell the master about the children?

79
00:07:55,933 --> 00:08:00,731
这与我无关。这是那两个小野兽最后一次从我这溜走。
It's no concern of mine. Those little beasts have run away from me for the last time.

80
00:08:00,981 --> 00:08:03,943
他们一定在什么地方。你去动物园找过了么？
They must be somewhere. Did you look around the zoo in the park?

81
00:08:04,193 --> 00:08:05,862
你了解简和迈克尔
You know how Jane and Michael is.

82
00:08:06,112 --> 00:08:08,948
你难道不担心狮子会抓住他们吗？
Coo! You don't think the lion could've got at them, do ya?

83
00:08:09,199 --> 00:08:11,535
你知道他们是多喜欢在那笼子周围玩
You know how fond they was of hangin' around the cage.

84
00:08:11,785 --> 00:08:13,746
我不想再废话了
I said my say, and that's all I'll say.

85
00:08:13,996 --> 00:08:16,540
这所房子已经和我永远一刀两断
I've done with this house forever.

86
00:08:16,791 --> 00:08:18,293
好啊，好极了
Well, hip, hip, hooray!

87
00:08:18,543 --> 00:08:21,338
出门当心别摔了，宝贝
And don't stumble on the way out, dearie.

88
00:08:21,588 --> 00:08:25,718
噢，别这样，卡蒂保姆！
Now, now, Katie Nanna!

89
00:08:26,135 --> 00:08:29,263
班克斯夫人！她回来了！
Mrs Banks! She's home!

90
00:08:29,514 --> 00:08:32,726
我们女儿的女儿会敬仰我们 我们将一起欢唱
Our daughter's daughters will adore us and we'll sing in grateful chorus

91
00:08:32,976 --> 00:08:34,812
“干得好，主张参政的姐妹们”
"Well done, Sister Suffragette"

92
00:08:35,062 --> 00:08:37,064
卡蒂保姆，艾伦，晚上好
Good evening, Katie Nanna, Ellen.

93
00:08:37,314 --> 00:08:39,317
我们举行了一场盛大的聚会！
We had the most glorious meeting!

94
00:08:39,567 --> 00:08:43,738
威伯尼夫人把自己绑在首相的马车车轮上
Mrs Whitbourne-Allen chained herself to the wheel of the Prime Minister's carriage.

95
00:08:43,989 --> 00:08:46,200
你们真应该去看看
班克斯夫人，我有句话要对你说
You should've been there.
Mrs Banks, I would like a word with you.

96
00:08:46,450 --> 00:08:48,828
还有阿什列夫人被抓走了
And Mrs Ainslie, she was carried off to prison...

97
00:08:49,078 --> 00:08:50,997
她一路上边唱歌边散发传单
singing and scattering pamphlets all the way!

98
00:08:51,247 --> 00:08:54,084
我很高兴你回来了，夫人，我已经尽力了
I'm glad you're home, madam. I've always given the best that's in me...

99
00:08:54,334 --> 00:08:56,503
谢谢你，卡蒂保姆
Oh, thank you, Katie Nanna.

100
00:08:56,753 --> 00:08:59,131
我就知道我不会看错的
I always knew you were one of us.

101
00:08:59,382 --> 00:09:03,136
我们是身着裙装的战士
We're clearly soldiers in petticoats

102
00:09:03,386 --> 00:09:07,140
为妇女的投票权而英勇地战斗
And dauntless crusaders for women's votes

103
00:09:07,391 --> 00:09:11,270
尽管我们尊敬每一个男人
Though we adore men individually

104
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:16,026
但作为一个群体，他们是愚蠢的
We agree that as a group they're rather stupid

105
00:09:16,276 --> 00:09:20,614
班克斯夫人
甩掉昨日的枷锁
Mrs Banks.
Cast off the shackles of yesterday

106
00:09:20,865 --> 00:09:24,243
肩并肩，我们走向自由
Shoulder to shoulder into the fray

107
00:09:24,494 --> 00:09:27,956
我们女儿的女儿将会敬仰我们
Our daughter's daughters will adore us

108
00:09:28,206 --> 00:09:32,253
她们将一齐欢唱
And they'll sing in grateful chorus

109
00:09:32,503 --> 00:09:35,381
“干得好 主张参政的姐妹们”
"Well done Sister Suffragette"

110
00:09:35,632 --> 00:09:38,635
可能的话，我不想冒犯你，但是……
Being that as it may, I do not wish to offend, but I...

111
00:09:38,885 --> 00:09:42,515
从肯辛顿到比林斯门呼声此起彼伏
From Kensington to Billingsgate one hears the restless cries

112
00:09:42,765 --> 00:09:46,477
从这片土地的每一个角落 妇女们站起来了
From every corner of the land womankind arise

113
00:09:46,728 --> 00:09:50,440
政治平等 权利平等
Political equality and equal rights with men

114
00:09:50,691 --> 00:09:54,987
潘克赫斯特夫人又被铐上
Take heart for Mrs Pankhurst has been clapped in irons again

115
00:09:55,238 --> 00:10:01,036
我们不再做温顺的附属品
No more the meek and mild subservients we

116
00:10:01,286 --> 00:10:05,750
为了我们的权力英勇奋斗
We're fighting for our rights militantly

117
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,376
Never you fear

118
00:10:07,627 --> 00:10:11,214
班克斯夫人，我能插句话么？
If I may have a word, Mrs Banks.

119
00:10:11,465 --> 00:10:15,469
甩掉昨日的枷锁
班克斯夫人！
So cast off the shackles of yesterday
Mrs Banks!

120
00:10:15,719 --> 00:10:19,098
肩并肩我们走向自由
And shoulder to shoulder into the fray

121
00:10:19,349 --> 00:10:23,604
我们女儿的女儿将会敬仰我们
Our daughter's daughters will adore us

122
00:10:23,854 --> 00:10:28,276
她们将一齐欢唱
And they'll sing in grateful chorus

123
00:10:28,526 --> 00:10:30,445
“干得好”
班克斯夫人
"Well done"
Mrs Banks.

124
00:10:30,695 --> 00:10:32,322
“干得好”
班克斯夫人
"Well done"
Mrs Banks.

125
00:10:32,572 --> 00:10:34,783
班克斯夫人！
"Well done, Sister Suf..."
Mrs Banks!

126
00:10:35,033 --> 00:10:40,164
什么事？
班克斯夫人，我有件事要告诉你
What is it, Katie Nanna?
Mrs Banks, I have something to say to you.

127
00:10:40,415 --> 00:10:43,668
孩子们在哪里？
夫人，孩子们……
Where are the children?
The children, madam...

128
00:10:43,919 --> 00:10:45,712
确切地讲，不在这里
to be precise, are not here.

129
00:10:45,963 --> 00:10:47,715
他们又消失了
They've disappeared again.

130
00:10:47,965 --> 00:10:50,051
卡蒂保姆，你确实太粗心了
Katie Nanna, this is really too careless of you.

131
00:10:50,301 --> 00:10:52,095
这已经是这周的第三次了
Doesn't it make the third time this week?

132
00:10:52,345 --> 00:10:56,058
第四次，夫人。如果不是气愤之极的话
The fourth, madam. And I for one have had my fill of it.

133
00:10:56,308 --> 00:10:57,559
我并不想说他们的坏话
I'm not one to speak ill of the children, but...

134
00:10:57,810 --> 00:11:00,020
你估计他们什么时候能回来？
Oh, please, when do you expect them home?

135
00:11:00,271 --> 00:11:04,025
这可不好说。现在请你算一算我的薪水
I really couldn't say. And now if you'd be good enough to compute my wages, I'll...

136
00:11:04,275 --> 00:11:08,405
噢，天，卡蒂保姆！你不是要走吧？
班克斯先生会怎么说？
Oh, gracious, Katie Nanna! You're not leaving? What will Mr Banks say?

137
00:11:08,655 --> 00:11:11,951
他回家后，发现孩子们不见了会很生气的
He's going to be cross enough as it is to come home and find the children missing.

138
00:11:12,201 --> 00:11:15,497
艾伦，把这些拿开，你知道这东西会让他多恼火
Ellen, put these things away. You know how the cause infuriates Mr Banks.

139
00:11:15,747 --> 00:11:17,415
是的，妇人
Yes, ma'am.

140
00:11:17,666 --> 00:11:20,586
卡蒂保姆，我请求你，再想一想
Katie Nanna, I beseech you. Please reconsider.

141
00:11:20,836 --> 00:11:23,256
想想孩子们，想想班克斯先生
Think of the children. Think of Mr Banks.

142
00:11:23,506 --> 00:11:27,677
他刚开始适应你
He was just beginning to get used to you.

143
00:11:29,388 --> 00:11:32,391
各就各位！
Posts, everyone!

144
00:11:37,814 --> 00:11:44,321
4，3，2，1，点火！
Four, three, two, one. Fire!

145
00:11:55,835 --> 00:12:01,341
卡蒂保姆，我请求你……
我的薪水，请！
Katie Nanna, I do beseech you...
My wages, if you please.

146
00:12:03,594 --> 00:12:05,429
今晚早了点，是吗？将军
Bit early tonight, aren't you, Admiral?

147
00:12:05,679 --> 00:12:08,766
胡说，正点报时，跟往常一样
Nonsense. Bang on the dot, as usual.

148
00:12:09,017 --> 00:12:11,186
银行里的事情还好吧？
How are things in the world of finance?

149
00:12:11,436 --> 00:12:15,691
从没有比现在更好的时候了，货币坚挺，贷款利率不断上升
Never better. Money's sound. Credit rates are moving up, up, up.

150
00:12:15,941 --> 00:12:18,653
英镑成了全世界的宠物
And the British pound is the admiration of the world.

151
00:12:18,903 --> 00:12:21,072
很好
先生，你那儿的情况怎么样？
Good man.
How do things look from where you stand?

152
00:12:21,322 --> 00:12:23,700
很难讲
Bit chancy, I'd say.

153
00:12:23,950 --> 00:12:26,370
起风了，气压也下降了
The wind's coming up and the glass is falling.

154
00:12:26,620 --> 00:12:29,248
我不喜欢这种情况
好，好，好
Don't like the look of it.
Good, good, good.

155
00:12:29,499 --> 00:12:34,129
班克斯，毫无疑问你将赶上坏天气的
Banks, shouldn't wonder if you weren't steering into a nasty piece of weather.

156
00:12:34,379 --> 00:12:38,676
班克斯！你听见了么？
Banks! Do you hear me?

157
00:12:39,677 --> 00:12:41,846
你好，卡蒂保姆。那一定很重吧。
Hello, Katie Nanna. That must be heavy.

158
00:12:42,096 --> 00:12:45,726
让我来吧
Allow me.

159
00:12:45,976 --> 00:12:47,644
哼！
Hmph!

160
00:12:47,895 --> 00:12:51,357
多可爱的帽子啊！
What a very pretty hat.

161
00:12:57,072 --> 00:13:00,826
就像一位国王
I feel a surge of deep satisfaction

162
00:13:01,077 --> 00:13:04,789
骑着他的骏马，谢谢
Much as a king astride his noble steed Thank you.

163
00:13:05,039 --> 00:13:09,211
当我摆脱白天的喧嚣，回到家，回到妻子身边
When I return from daily strife to hearth and wife

164
00:13:09,461 --> 00:13:12,173
我是多么心满意足，我的生活多么愉快！
How pleasant is the life I lead

165
00:13:12,423 --> 00:13:14,509
亲爱的，有件事和孩子们有关
是的，是的，是的
Dear, it's about the children.
Yes, yes, yes.

166
00:13:14,759 --> 00:13:18,388
我按照日程表精确地管理着我的家！
I run my home precisely on schedule

167
00:13:18,638 --> 00:13:22,351
6点01分 我走进家门
At 6:01 I march through my door

168
00:13:22,601 --> 00:13:26,356
6点02分 放下我的手套和手杖
My slippers, sherry and pipe are due at 6:02

169
00:13:26,606 --> 00:13:29,276
我的生活始终如一！
Consistent is the life I lead

170
00:13:29,526 --> 00:13:32,404
乔治，孩子们不见了。
太美妙了。
George, they're missing.
Splendid. Splendid.

171
00:13:32,655 --> 00:13:36,284
1910年在爱德华国王的统治下
It's grand to be an Englishman in 1910

172
00:13:36,534 --> 00:13:39,788
做一位英国男人是多么光荣 这是一个男人唯上的时代
King Edward's on the throne It's the Age of Men

173
00:13:40,038 --> 00:13:43,792
我是城堡的主人 统治者
I'm the lord of my castle The sovereign, the liege

174
00:13:44,043 --> 00:13:47,380
我管理着我的仆人，孩子们和妻子
I treat my subjects, servants children, wife

175
00:13:47,630 --> 00:13:49,883
严格且温和，贵族的行为理应高尚
With a firm but gentle hand Noblesse oblige

176
00:13:50,133 --> 00:13:53,721
现在6点03分，我领地的继承人们
It's 6:03 and the heirs to my dominion

177
00:13:53,971 --> 00:13:57,558
已经洗过了，吃饱了
Are scrubbed and tubbed and adequately fed

178
00:13:57,809 --> 00:14:01,646
我会拍拍他们的头，打发他们去睡觉
And so I'll pat them on the head
and send them off to bed

179
00:14:01,897 --> 00:14:08,529
啊，我的生活多么气派！
Ah, lordly is the life I lead

180
00:14:08,863 --> 00:14:12,576
威妮弗蕾德，孩子们在哪儿？
他们不在这里，亲爱的
Winifred, where are the children?
They're not here, dear.

181
00:14:12,826 --> 00:14:16,163
什么？他们当然应该在这儿！他们会在别的地方吗？
What? Well, of course they're here!
Where else would they be?

182
00:14:16,413 --> 00:14:19,584
我不知道，乔治
你不知道？
I don't know, George.
You don't know?

183
00:14:19,834 --> 00:14:23,463
他们不见了。卡蒂保姆到处都找遍了
Well, they're missing. Katie Nanna has looked everywhere.

184
00:14:23,713 --> 00:14:27,509
我要立即处理这件事
Very well. I'll deal with this at once.

185
00:14:30,346 --> 00:14:32,265
请给我接警察局，快！
Give me the police station, quickly, please.

186
00:14:32,515 --> 00:14:36,019
我想这件事不必麻烦警察，事实上……
I don't think we need bother the police, dear. The facts of the matter...

187
00:14:36,270 --> 00:14:38,022
请别试图用什么事实把事情弄得模糊不清
Kindly do not attempt to cloud the issue with facts.

188
00:14:38,272 --> 00:14:42,235
唯一的事实，很明显，卡蒂保姆不能胜任她的工作
One fact, and one fact alone is crystal clear! Katie Nanna's faltered at her post.

189
00:14:42,485 --> 00:14:46,531
她使得这个家陷入混乱，我要教训教训她……
She's let the family down. And I shall bring her to bo...

190
00:14:46,782 --> 00:14:50,161
哦，她已经走了，是吗？
Oh. She's left us, hasn't she?

191
00:14:50,411 --> 00:14:52,580
是的，亲爱的，刚刚走
Yes, dear, only just.

192
00:14:52,830 --> 00:14:54,874
喂，呃……我是乔治?班克斯
What, uh... Yes. George Banks here.

193
00:14:55,125 --> 00:14:59,296
樱桃树大街17号。出了件急事
Yes. 17 Cherry Tree Lane. It's a matter of some urgency.

194
00:14:59,546 --> 00:15:02,800
请立即派一名警察
I should like you to send a policeman around immediately.

195
00:15:03,050 --> 00:15:04,469
乔治，警察来了！
The policeman's here, George!

196
00:15:04,719 --> 00:15:08,640
什么？噢，真及时！服务真好！
What? Oh, how very prompt. What wonderful service.

197
00:15:08,890 --> 00:15:11,560
谢谢！晚安
Thank you so much. Good night.

198
00:15:11,810 --> 00:15:13,646
请进，警察先生，请进！
谢谢！
Come in, Constable. Come in.
Thank you, sir.

199
00:15:13,896 --> 00:15:16,441
我在公园那边巡逻时
While going about my duties on the other side of the park...

200
00:15:16,691 --> 00:15:18,485
发现了两件遗失的贵重物品
I noted some valuables that had gone astray.

201
00:15:18,735 --> 00:15:20,988
我相信是你的，先生
贵重物品？
I believe they're yours, sir.
Valuables?

202
00:15:21,238 --> 00:15:25,034
来，过来
Come along, now. Come along.

203
00:15:25,827 --> 00:15:28,913
简！迈克尔！
Jane! Michael!

204
00:15:29,164 --> 00:15:30,665
威妮弗蕾德，请别激动
Winifred, please don't be emotional.

205
00:15:30,916 --> 00:15:35,087
哦，他们今天走了很多路，精疲力尽了
Oh, I wouldn't be too hard on 'em, sir. They've had a long, weary walk today.

206
00:15:35,338 --> 00:15:39,259
孩子们，过来
Children, come here at once.

207
00:15:42,763 --> 00:15:45,850
怎么回事？
对不起，我们和保姆卡蒂走散了
Well?
I'm sorry we lost Katie Nanna, Father.

208
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:50,021
你知道的，今天风很大，而这个风筝对我们来说大了点
You see, it was windy. And the kite was too strong for us.

209
00:15:50,271 --> 00:15:54,026
在某种意义上说，先生，是风筝跑走了而不是孩子们
In a manner of speaking, sir, it was the kite that ran away, not the children.

210
00:15:54,276 --> 00:15:56,529
谢谢，警察先生。我想我能够控制这件事
Thank you, Constable. I think I can manage this.

211
00:15:56,779 --> 00:16:01,368
说实话，这风筝并不好。我们自己做的
Actually it wasn't a very good kite. We made it ourselves.

212
00:16:01,618 --> 00:16:03,328
也许你可以帮我们做一个……
Perhaps if you helped us to make one...

213
00:16:03,578 --> 00:16:07,333
哦，那很重要，先生。风筝很难控制
Ah, that's the ticket, sir. Kites are skittish things.

214
00:16:07,583 --> 00:16:09,126
就在上周，我和我的孩子们……
Why, only last week with me own youngsters...

215
00:16:09,377 --> 00:16:11,796
我非常感谢你送他们回来
I'm very grateful to you, Constable, for returning the children.

216
00:16:12,046 --> 00:16:16,176
如果你到厨房看看，厨师会给你弄些吃的
And I'm sure that if you go to the kitchen, Cook'll find you a plate of something.

217
00:16:16,427 --> 00:16:19,555
谢谢你，先生。我该回去工作了
Thank you, sir. I shall now return to my duties.

218
00:16:19,805 --> 00:16:21,891
谢谢你，警察先生
Thank you, Constable.

219
00:16:22,141 --> 00:16:26,104
晚安，小姐。晚安，夫人，晚安，先生
Good night, miss. Good night, ma'am.
Good night, sir.

220
00:16:26,355 --> 00:16:30,192
厨师会给我弄些吃的。我从没……
Cook'll find me something. I never...

221
00:16:31,778 --> 00:16:34,739
乔治，我非常非常抱歉
I'm awfully sorry about this, George.

222
00:16:34,990 --> 00:16:37,075
我猜你大概要谈谈这件事
I'll expect you'll want to discuss it.

223
00:16:37,326 --> 00:16:39,328
的确！
I would indeed!

224
00:16:39,578 --> 00:16:41,747
艾伦，带简和迈克尔到楼上去
Ellen, take Jane and Michael upstairs straightaway.

225
00:16:41,998 --> 00:16:45,085
好的，先生
Yes, sir.

226
00:16:45,335 --> 00:16:50,174
我就知道。谁首当其冲的负担这一切？
I knew it. When all's said and done, who bears the brunt of everything around here?

227
00:16:50,424 --> 00:16:51,801
我！就是这样！
Me, that's who!

228
00:16:52,051 --> 00:16:55,555
他们不想要一个诚实勤劳的人
They don't want an honest, hard-workin' girl around here.

229
00:16:55,805 --> 00:16:59,101
他们需要的是动物园看守
They need a ruddy zookeeper.

230
00:16:59,351 --> 00:17:02,354
我很抱歉，亲爱的。我当初之所以选中了卡蒂保姆……
I'm sorry, dear, but when I chose Katie Nanna...

231
00:17:02,605 --> 00:17:04,440
是因为她看上去那么严厉
I thought she would be firm with the children.

232
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:06,484
她看上去会严格地要求孩子们。
She looked so solemn and cross.

233
00:17:06,734 --> 00:17:10,113
威妮弗蕾德，不要把效率和急躁混为一谈
Winifred, never confuse efficiency with a liver complaint.

234
00:17:10,364 --> 00:17:12,116
下次我会试着干得好一点
I'll try to do better next time.

235
00:17:12,366 --> 00:17:15,203
下次？亲爱的，过去的四个月里你已经换了六个保姆
Next time? My dear, you've engaged six nannies in the last four months!

236
00:17:15,453 --> 00:17:18,999
个个都是不称职的灾星
我同意
And they've all been unqualified disasters.
I quite agree.

237
00:17:19,249 --> 00:17:22,127
给孩子们选保姆是一项重要而细致的任务
Choosing a nanny for the children is an important and delicate task.

238
00:17:22,377 --> 00:17:27,634
它要求深入的观察，公正的判断，还有识别人的能力
It requires insight, balanced judgment, and an ability to read character.

239
00:17:27,884 --> 00:17:32,139
在这种情况下，只好由我亲自来……
Under the circumstances, I think it might be apropos to take it upon myself to, uh...

240
00:17:32,389 --> 00:17:34,266
呃，处理了
select the next person.

241
00:17:34,516 --> 00:17:36,852
噢，乔治？！
显然想要选出一位合适的保姆
Oh, would you, George?
Obviously the way to find a proper nanny...

242
00:17:37,103 --> 00:17:38,938
就应该采用恰当的方式
is to go about it in a proper fashion.

243
00:17:39,189 --> 00:17:41,900
我要在《泰晤士报》上登一则广告。请你记下来
I shall put an advertisement in the Times. Take this down please.

244
00:17:42,150 --> 00:17:43,902
当然，是的，亲爱的。
招聘
Yes, of course, dear.
Wanted.

245
00:17:44,153 --> 00:17:46,155
呃，不，呃，要求一位……
Uh, no. Uh, required.

246
00:17:46,405 --> 00:17:51,369
严厉、受人尊敬言谈稳重的保姆
Nanny: Firm, respectable, no nonsense.

247
00:17:51,620 --> 00:17:55,290
以为英国的保姆应该像一位将军
A British nanny must be a general

248
00:17:55,541 --> 00:17:58,920
帝国的未来就掌握在她的手中
The future empire lies within her hands

249
00:17:59,170 --> 00:18:03,091
因此我们需要塑造孩童的人
And so the person that we need
to mould the breed

250
00:18:03,341 --> 00:18:06,011
应该是一位能够发号施令的保姆
Is a nanny who can give commands

251
00:18:06,261 --> 00:18:08,639
你记下来了么，威妮弗蕾德？
噢，是的，亲爱的，一字不差
You getting this, Winifred?
Oh, yes, dear. Every word.

252
00:18:08,889 --> 00:18:12,477
一家英国银行的运作在准确无误的基础上
A British bank is run with precision

253
00:18:12,727 --> 00:18:16,189
一个英国家庭也要求丝毫不差
A British home requires nothing less

254
00:18:16,440 --> 00:18:21,154
传统，纪律和规则是我们的工具
Tradition, discipline and rules
must be the tools

255
00:18:21,404 --> 00:18:25,700
失去了这些，将陷入混乱，灾难，无政府状态
Without them, disorder catastrophe, anarchy

256
00:18:25,951 --> 00:18:29,580
总之，可怕的混乱
In short you have a ghastly mess

257
00:18:29,830 --> 00:18:31,874
精辟，乔治！很有启迪
Splendid, George! Inspirational.

258
00:18:32,124 --> 00:18:33,918
《泰晤士报》会很满意的
The Times will be so pleased.

259
00:18:34,169 --> 00:18:36,546
父亲？
什么？
Father?
Yes?

260
00:18:36,797 --> 00:18:39,049
我们已经商量过了
We've discussed everything...

261
00:18:39,299 --> 00:18:41,510
对今天的所做作为，我们感到非常抱歉
and we're very sorry about what we did today.

262
00:18:41,761 --> 00:18:43,805
我想应该是的
I should certainly think so.

263
00:18:44,055 --> 00:18:46,558
从卡蒂保姆那里跑走是不应该的
是这样
It was wrong to run away from Katie Nanna.
It was indeed.

264
00:18:46,808 --> 00:18:48,894
我们这么干的目的就是想要换一位新的保姆
And we do so want to get on with the new nanny.

265
00:18:49,144 --> 00:18:52,064
很明智。我很高兴在这件事上能得到你们的帮助
Very sensible. I shall be glad to have your help in the matter.

266
00:18:52,314 --> 00:18:55,193
我们认为你会同意的。所以我们写了一份广告
We thought you would. That's why we wrote this advertisement.

267
00:18:55,443 --> 00:18:57,612
什么广告
招聘新保姆的
Advertisement for what?
For the new nanny.

268
00:18:57,862 --> 00:19:00,490
你们写了一份广告……
乔治，我想我们应该听一听
You wrote an advert...
George, I think we should listen.

269
00:19:00,741 --> 00:19:04,745
你说过你需要我们的帮助
但我是……哦，好吧
You said you wanted our help.
But, I... Oh, very well.

270
00:19:04,996 --> 00:19:08,249
为两位极其可爱的孩子招聘一个保姆
"Wanted: A nanny for two adorable children."

271
00:19:08,500 --> 00:19:10,961
及其可爱的？应该说是“极其难管”的
"Adorable." Well, that's debatable, I must say.

272
00:19:11,211 --> 00:19:15,424
如果你想得到这个职位
If you want this choice position

273
00:19:15,675 --> 00:19:19,763
你应该开朗活泼
Have a cheery disposition

274
00:19:20,013 --> 00:19:24,351
简，我不是……
面庞红润，没有疣子
Jane, I don't...
Rosy cheeks, no warts

275
00:19:24,602 --> 00:19:29,232
那是我加进去的
精通各种游戏
That's the part I put in.
Play games, all sorts

276
00:19:29,482 --> 00:19:34,154
你必须善良和蔼，聪明机智
You must be kind You must be witty

277
00:19:34,405 --> 00:19:38,201
恬美可爱，且美丽漂亮
Very sweet and fairly pretty

278
00:19:38,451 --> 00:19:39,494
好了，简直荒唐透顶……
乔治，别这样！
Well, of all the ridic...
George, please!

279
00:19:39,744 --> 00:19:43,832
带我们出游 款待我们
Take us on outings Give us treats

280
00:19:44,082 --> 00:19:47,628
为我们唱歌 还要带上甜点
Sing songs Bring sweets

281
00:19:47,878 --> 00:19:50,673
从不发火
Never be cross or cruel

282
00:19:50,924 --> 00:19:56,638
绝不拿蓖麻油和薄粥糊弄我们
Never give us castor oil or gruel

283
00:19:56,889 --> 00:20:00,518
爱我们如同自己的子女
Love us as a son and daughter

284
00:20:00,768 --> 00:20:05,524
还有不能有大麦茶味儿
And never smell of barley water

285
00:20:05,774 --> 00:20:08,986
这条也是我加进去的
I put that in too.

286
00:20:09,236 --> 00:20:13,616
如果你不斥责我们，压制我们
If you won't scold and dominate us

287
00:20:13,867 --> 00:20:19,456
我们绝不会做让你恨我们的事情
We will never you give you cause to hate us

288
00:20:19,707 --> 00:20:24,504
我们不会藏起你的眼镜，让你找不到
We won't hide your spectacles so you can't see

289
00:20:24,754 --> 00:20:30,177
把青蛙放在你的床上，或把胡椒粉倒进你的茶里
Put toads in your bed or pepper in your tea

290
00:20:30,427 --> 00:20:33,598
好保姆，快点来
Hurry, Nanny

291
00:20:33,848 --> 00:20:38,520
此致……敬礼
Many thanks Sincerely

292
00:20:38,770 --> 00:20:43,568
简和迈克尔?班克斯敬上
Jane and Michael Banks

293
00:20:43,818 --> 00:20:45,570
谢谢。非常有趣
Thank you. Most interesting.

294
00:20:45,820 --> 00:20:47,364
现在我听够了你们的胡言乱语
And now I think we've had quite enough of this nonsense.

295
00:20:47,614 --> 00:20:52,161
回房间去吧
Please return to the nursery.

296
00:21:02,631 --> 00:21:04,800
他们毕竟是个小孩子，他们只是想帮帮忙
They were only trying to help. They're just children.

297
00:21:05,051 --> 00:21:06,886
我知道他们还是小孩子
I'm well aware they're just children, Winifred.

298
00:21:07,136 --> 00:21:09,723
我很庆幸我决定介入这件事情
I only congratulate myself that I decided to step in and take a hand.

299
00:21:09,973 --> 00:21:13,268
“游戏，唱歌，甜点”
"Play games, sing songs, give treats."

300
00:21:13,519 --> 00:21:16,898
荒唐！毫无疑问
Ridiculous. There's no question in my mind whatsoever.

301
00:21:17,148 --> 00:21:20,902
该开始行动了
Now is the time for action.

302
00:21:21,194 --> 00:21:24,907
请告诉我《泰晤士报》的号码 不，我当然不知道号码
Give me the Times, please. No, I do not know the number.

303
00:21:25,157 --> 00:21:27,618
哦，乔治，你总是这么强势
Oh, George, you're always so forceful.

304
00:21:27,869 --> 00:21:29,829
泰晤士报？我是乔治?班克斯
The Times? George Banks here.

305
00:21:30,079 --> 00:21:35,794
樱桃树大街17号。我要在你们的栏目上登一则广告
17 Cherry Tree Lane. I wish to place an advertisement in your column.

306
00:21:51,938 --> 00:21:54,775
报时枪准备好了么？
准备完毕，将军！
Time gun ready?
Ready and charged, sir.

307
00:21:55,025 --> 00:21:57,403
请报告，宾纳克先生
I'll take the report, Mr Binnacle.

308
00:21:57,653 --> 00:22:01,449
是。风向已经转变，好像来自一个新的区域
The wind has changed, sir. Seems
to be comin' in from a new quarter.

309
00:22:01,699 --> 00:22:04,244
是的
先生？
什么事？
So it is.
Sir?
What is it?

310
00:22:04,494 --> 00:22:09,083
左舷船首好像出事了
Bit of somethin' or other taking place off the port bow.

311
00:22:10,042 --> 00:22:15,090
我不得不说，一群可怕的人
Ghastly looking crew, I must say!

312
00:22:20,638 --> 00:22:24,642
门外的保姆排起了长队，先生。能让她们进来了么？
Coo! There's a fair queue of nannies outside, sir. Shall I show 'em in?

313
00:22:24,893 --> 00:22:28,105
艾伦，我说过了8点钟开始，就8点
Ellen, I said 8:00, and 8:00 it shall jolly well be.

314
00:22:28,355 --> 00:22:30,149
还有12秒
You see? Twelve seconds to go.

315
00:22:30,399 --> 00:22:33,152
10，9，8…… 各就各位！
Ten, nine, eight... Posts!

316
00:22:33,402 --> 00:22:36,781
7，6，5，4……
Seven, six, five, four...

317
00:22:37,032 --> 00:22:40,202
3，2，1！
three, two, one!

318
00:22:40,452 --> 00:22:44,373
艾伦，现在8点整了
Ellen, it is now 8:00.

319
00:22:45,917 --> 00:22:46,960
是的，先生
Yes, sir.

320
00:22:47,210 --> 00:22:49,838
艾伦，我已经告诉你多遍……
But I have told you time and time again, Ellen...

321
00:22:50,088 --> 00:22:52,675
我不喜欢做事没有条理
I dislike being hurried into things.

322
00:22:52,925 --> 00:22:58,932
我不明白，他们一点也不符合咱们的广告
I don't understand. They're not what we advertised for at all.

323
00:23:47,363 --> 00:23:50,533
迈克尔，看！
Michael, look!

324
00:23:55,414 --> 00:23:57,082
不会是一个巫婆吧。
Perhaps it's a witch.

325
00:23:57,332 --> 00:24:01,212
当然不是，巫婆都是骑着扫把
Of course not. Witches have brooms.

326
00:24:15,937 --> 00:24:19,900
就是她，咱们想要的人。她看了我们的广告
It's her. It's the person. She's answered our advertisement.

327
00:24:20,150 --> 00:24:24,989
