Oh.

332
00:24:44,595 --> 00:24:49,059
你就是简和迈克尔的父亲吗？
You are the father of Jane and Michael Banks, are you not?

333
00:24:49,809 --> 00:24:52,354
我说，你是简和迈克尔的父亲吗？
I said, you are the father of Jane and Michael Banks.

334
00:24:52,604 --> 00:24:54,982
噢，是的，当然
Well, well ye... Yes, of course, I mean. Uh...

335
00:24:55,232 --> 00:24:57,151
你带了推荐信吧？我可以看看吗？
You brought your references, I presume. May I see them?

336
00:24:57,402 --> 00:24:59,320
哦，我的原则是不提供推荐信
Oh, I make it a point never to give references.

337
00:24:59,571 --> 00:25:01,448
依我看，那已经过时了
A very old-fashioned idea to my mind.

338
00:25:01,698 --> 00:25:04,410
是么？我们还是有必要看一看
Is that so? We'll have to see about that then, won't we?

339
00:25:04,660 --> 00:25:07,955
现在，看看广告上的要求吧
Now then, the qualifications.

340
00:25:08,206 --> 00:25:10,709
第一条：开朗活泼
"Item one: A cheery disposition."

341
00:25:10,959 --> 00:25:12,711
我从不生气
I am never cross.

342
00:25:12,961 --> 00:25:15,798
第二条：面庞红润
"Item two: Rosy cheeks."

343
00:25:16,048 --> 00:25:17,383
显而易见
Obviously.

344
00:25:17,633 --> 00:25:21,304
第三条：会做各种游戏
"Item three: Play games, all sorts."

345
00:25:21,554 --> 00:25:24,016
我可以肯定孩子们会发现我的游戏花样繁多
Well, I'm sure the children will find my games extremely diverting.

346
00:25:24,266 --> 00:25:27,561
这张纸，你从哪里弄到的？我记得我已经把它撕了
May I? Eh, this paper? Where did you get it from? I thought I tore it up.

347
00:25:27,812 --> 00:25:31,649
抱歉，第四条：必须善良和蔼
Excuse me. "Item four: You must be kind."

348
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:34,903
我很善良，但非常严格
I am kind, but extremely firm.

349
00:25:35,153 --> 00:25:37,197
你丢了什么东西吗？
啊！是
Have you lost something?
Ah! Yeah.

350
00:25:37,448 --> 00:25:40,201
那张纸，我想我……
That paper, you see. I thought that I...

351
00:25:40,451 --> 00:25:42,829
你是乔治?班克斯先生吗？
什么？
You are George Banks, are you not?
What?

352
00:25:43,079 --> 00:25:45,957
你登了广告招聘保姆，是吗？
And you did advertise for a nanny, did you not?

353
00:25:46,208 --> 00:25:49,879
乔治?班克斯
那就好
George Banks.
Very well then.

354
00:25:50,129 --> 00:25:52,757
我撕了它，转过来
I tore it up, turned it over.

355
00:25:53,007 --> 00:25:55,051
又撕了一下，然后扔在哪儿
Tore it up again and threw it in there. Yes.

356
00:25:55,302 --> 00:25:58,180
请原谅，你生病了吗？
I beg your pardon. Are you ill?

357
00:25:58,430 --> 00:26:00,933
我希望没有
I hope not.

358
00:26:01,183 --> 00:26:04,270
现在谈谈我的薪水吧。关于这一点这上面很模糊
Now, about my wages. The reference here is very obscure.

359
00:26:04,521 --> 00:26:06,982
是很模糊
我们有必要明确下来
Very obscure.
We must be very clear on that point, mustn't we?

360
00:26:07,232 --> 00:26:09,735
的确有必要
每隔一个星期二我得休息一天
Yes, we must indeed.
I shall require every second Tuesday off.

361
00:26:09,985 --> 00:26:13,698
每个星期二
Every Tuesday.

362
00:26:15,742 --> 00:26:20,289
另外，规定一个试用期也许是明智的做法
On second thoughts, I believe
a trial period would be wise.

363
00:26:25,461 --> 00:26:31,051
我给你一个星期的时间
Hmm. I'll give you one week.
I'll know by then.

364
00:26:32,386 --> 00:26:36,265
我去看看孩子们，谢谢你
I'll see the children now. Thank you.

365
00:26:49,614 --> 00:26:54,536
迈克尔，把你的嘴闭上，我们不是鳕鱼
Close your mouth please, Michael. We are not a codfish.

366
00:26:55,704 --> 00:26:58,416
