01:15:17,929 --> 01:15:21,016
伯特，你呢？
噢，不，不，不要糖
Uh, Bert?
Uh, no, no, thank you. No sugar for me.

952
01:15:21,266 --> 01:15:24,728
我很高兴你上来。如果你不来的话，就不好玩了
I'm so glad you came. It wouldn't be any fun without you.

953
01:15:24,978 --> 01:15:28,023
给你自己还有迈克尔加点牛奶
Here, and you may pour some milk for Michael and yourself.

954
01:15:28,273 --> 01:15:30,192
你不觉得今年的这个时候天气非常的好吗？
Nice weather we're having this time of year, don't you think?

955
01:15:30,442 --> 01:15:32,652
哦，是的。呃，谈到天气……
Oh, yeah. Uh, speaking of weather...

956
01:15:32,903 --> 01:15:34,863
有一天，天很冷
the other day when it was so cold...

957
01:15:35,113 --> 01:15:38,575
我的一个朋友想去买件长一点的内衣
a friend of mine went to buy some long underwear, you know.

958
01:15:38,825 --> 01:15:41,870
售货员问，你打算要多长的（也可理解为：你打算要穿多久的）
The shopkeeper said to him, "How long do you want it?"

959
01:15:42,120 --> 01:15:47,167
我的朋友回答说，大概从9月到3月
And my friend said, "Well, from about September to March."

960
01:15:50,170 --> 01:15:54,341
简！别太放肆了！
Jane! Control yourself!

961
01:15:54,591 --> 01:15:58,929
孩子们，麻烦你们坐到桌子旁边来
Children, will you please sit up properly at the table?

962
01:15:59,179 --> 01:16:02,098
你的茶，艾伯特叔叔
噢，谢谢，亲爱的
Your tea, Uncle Albert.
Oh, thank you, my dear.

963
01:16:02,349 --> 01:16:07,604
我很开心，多么希望你们能一直留在这里啊
I'm having such a good time. I wish that you could all stay up here all the time.

964
01:16:07,854 --> 01:16:10,523
我们很高兴不得不留下，因为没有路下去
We'll jolly well have to. There's no way to get down.

965
01:16:10,774 --> 01:16:13,151
哦不，路是有的
Oh, no, there is a way.

966
01:16:13,401 --> 01:16:15,779
坦诚地讲，我不愿提起它……
Frankly I, I don't like to mention it...

967
01:16:16,029 --> 01:16:18,031
因为你得不得不想一些悲伤的事情
because you have to think of something sad.

968
01:16:18,281 --> 01:16:20,283
那么请开始吧
Then do get on with it, please!

969
01:16:20,533 --> 01:16:23,286
让我想想看
Let me see.

970
01:16:23,536 --> 01:16:25,789
我知道一件非常合适的事情
I've got the very thing.

971
01:16:26,039 --> 01:16:30,543
昨天隔壁的女士应声去开门，一个人站在门外
Yesterday when the lady next door answered the bell, there was a man there.

972
01:16:30,794 --> 01:16:35,799
他对女士说，我非常抱歉，我刚刚轧了你的猫
And the man said to the lady, "I'm terribly sorry. I just ran over your cat."

973
01:16:36,049 --> 01:16:39,511
哦，真悲惨
可怜的猫咪
Oh, that's sad.
The poor cat.

974
01:16:39,761 --> 01:16:42,806
接着，那个人说，我很愿意替代那只猫
And then the man said, "I'd like to replace your cat."

975
01:16:43,056 --> 01:16:47,894
女士说，可以，但有一点，你捉老鼠的技术好不好？
And the lady said, "That's all right with me, but how are you at catching mice?"

976
01:16:50,980 --> 01:16:54,317
我真的很努力让自己伤心点，但是……
Well, you know I started out sad. I, I try, really I do.

977
01:16:54,567 --> 01:16:58,947
一切都那么好笑，我不能……
But, but everything ends up so hilarious, I can't...

978
01:16:59,197 --> 01:17:02,492
我禁不住……
I can't help...

979
01:17:03,493 --> 01:17:07,038
这已经够了
That will be quite enough of that!

980
01:17:07,288 --> 01:17:09,499
我们该回家了
It's time to go home.

981
01:17:09,749 --> 01:17:11,334
唉，那太让人难过了
哦，不！
Oh, that is sad.
Oh, no!

982
01:17:11,584 --> 01:17:16,297
那是我听过的最难过的事情了
Oh, that's sad. That's the saddest thing I ever heard.

983
01:17:16,547 --> 01:17:18,341
来吧，孩子们
Come along, children. Spit spot!

984
01:17:18,591 --> 01:17:21,094
你们必须得走吗？
Must you really go?

985
01:17:21,344 --> 01:17:23,971
你知道，大家来看望我
You know, people come to see me all the time, you know.

986
01:17:24,222 --> 01:17:28,226
我们一起过得很愉快，然而他们不得不回家
And, and we have such a lovely time, and then they have to go home.

987
01:17:28,476 --> 01:17:32,438
对此我会感到非常非常的伤心
And, and I'm very, very sad about the whole thing.

988
01:17:32,688 --> 01:17:35,149
别难过，我们会很快再来的
Don't worry. We'll come back soon.

989
01:17:35,399 --> 01:17:37,193
我们过得非常开心
We had a lovely time.

990
01:17:37,443 --> 01:17:39,821
伯特，照顾好艾伯特叔叔，好吗？
Uh, keep an eye on Uncle Albert, will you, Bert?

991
01:17:40,071 --> 01:17:44,909
我会再陪他呆一会儿的
谢谢，来吧
I'll sit with him a while.
Thank you. Come on.

992
01:17:45,159 --> 01:17:49,789
艾伯特叔叔，我有一个笑话专门留给这样的场合的
Uncle Albert, I got a jolly joke I saved for just such an occasion.

993
01:17:50,039 --> 01:17:53,209
你想听听看吗？
好啊，我非常感激
Would you like to hear it?
I'd be so grateful.

994
01:17:53,459 --> 01:17:56,837
不必客气，这是关于我爷爷的
Righto. Well, it's about me granddad, see?

995
01:17:57,088 --> 01:17:59,340
有一天晚上，我爷爷做了一个恶梦
And one night, he had a nightmare, he did.

996
01:17:59,590 --> 01:18:02,343
他害怕极了，以至于把枕头咬成了碎片
So scared that he chewed his pillow to bits.
Yes.

997
01:18:02,593 --> 01:18:04,512
成了碎片……第二天早晨，我说……
To bits.
Yes.
Next morning I says...

998
01:18:04,762 --> 01:18:06,055
你感觉还好吗？爷爷？
"How do you feel, Granddad?"
Yes.

999
01:18:06,305 --> 01:18:11,852
他回答，呃，不坏，只是有点口干
He says, "Oh, not bad. A little down in the mouth!"

1000
01:18:15,856 --> 01:18:17,650
我常说，没有什么东西比得上一个好笑话
Yeah, I always say there's nothing like a good joke.

1001
01:18:17,900 --> 01:18:23,572
确实是，啥也比不上好笑话
No. And that was nothing like a good joke! That...

1002
01:18:38,170 --> 01:18:41,757
班克斯，你今晚晚了些，是吗？
Bit late tonight, aren't you, Banks?

1003
01:18:42,133 --> 01:18:45,928
我说，班克斯！出了什么问题了，班克斯？
I say, Banks! Is anything the matter, Banks?

1004
01:18:46,178 --> 01:18:50,140
班克斯！
Banks!

1005
01:18:54,478 --> 01:18:57,314
噢，父亲，真高兴你回来了
想听个笑话吗？
Oh, Father, we're so glad you're home!
Want to hear a joke?

1006
01:18:57,565 --> 01:19:00,025
我们今天下午和玛丽?泼平斯在一起过得非常愉快
We had the most wonderful afternoon with Mary Poppins.

1007
01:19:00,276 --> 01:19:02,611
说到下午的事情，那个笑话是这样的
Speaking of afternoons, the joke goes like this.

1008
01:19:02,861 --> 01:19:04,905
我知道有个人名字叫史密斯，他有条假腿
I know a man with a wooden leg named Smith.

1009
01:19:05,155 --> 01:19:07,950
史密斯？我们不认识叫史密斯的人
Smith? We don't know anyone called Smith.

1010
01:19:08,200 --> 01:19:12,746
笑话还没有讲完，另一个家伙问，他的另一条腿叫什么名字
And there was a second chap, and the second chap says,
"What's the name of his other leg?"

1011
01:19:12,997 --> 01:19:15,791
我们还在天花板上开了一个非常棒的茶会
And we had a lovely tea party on the ceiling!

1012
01:19:16,041 --> 01:19:17,668
哦，孩子们，请安静
Oh, children, please be quiet.

1013
01:19:17,918 --> 01:19:20,587
玛丽?泼平斯说，如果我们乖，她还会带我们去那儿的
Mary Poppins says if we're good, she'll take us there again.

1014
01:19:20,838 --> 01:19:25,134
哦，玛丽?泼平斯这样说的吗？
Oh. Oh, Mary Poppins said that, did she?

1015
01:19:25,384 --> 01:19:27,970
请回到你们自己的房间去，好吗？
Will you please return to your room.

1016
01:19:28,220 --> 01:19:31,682
玛丽?泼平斯，请随我来好吗？
Mary Poppins, will you be kind enough to come with me?

1017
01:19:31,932 --> 01:19:35,394
好的
As you wish.

1018
01:19:36,270 --> 01:19:41,692
玛丽?泼平斯，我很遗憾，有些话我不得不说
Mary Poppins, I very much regret what I must say to you.

1019
01:19:44,361 --> 01:19:47,739
晚上好，乔治，有什么问题吗？
我恐怕是的
Good evening, George. Is anything the matter?
I'm afraid there is.

1020
01:19:47,990 --> 01:19:51,285
我很想留下来，但是我不得不换衣服了，因为今晚还有个集会
I, I'd love to stay, but I have to dress for my rally in Hampstead.

1021
01:19:51,535 --> 01:19:53,453
威妮弗蕾德，我希望你能留下来
Winifred, it is my wish that you be present!

1022
01:19:53,704 --> 01:19:55,455
好的，乔治，当然
Oh, yes, George, of course.

1023
01:19:55,706 --> 01:19:59,626
玛丽?泼平斯，我不得不说，我对你感到非常失望
Mary Poppins, I must confess I am extremely disappointed in you.

1024
01:19:59,877 --> 01:20:03,338
终于轮到她了，我以前就听过主人这样讲话
She's for it now. I've heard the master do this speech before.

1025
01:20:03,589 --> 01:20:06,466
我不否认对于孩子们将全部的时间……
I don't deny that I am partially responsible for allowing the children...

1026
01:20:06,717 --> 01:20:10,470
都浪费在毫无意义的游戏上，我应该承担一定的责任
to spend their days on worthless frivolity to the exclusion of all else!

1027
01:20:10,721 --> 01:20:13,390
但是，现在已经到了让他们认识到生活的严肃性的时候
But it is high time they learned the seriousness of life!

1028
01:20:13,640 --> 01:20:15,559
但是，乔治，他们还是孩子
But, George, they're only children.

1029
01:20:15,809 --> 01:20:17,686
精确地讲，鉴于已经发生的……
Precisely. And in the light of what has happened...

1030
01:20:17,936 --> 01:20:20,147
乔治，你肯定你在说些什么吗？
George, are you certain you know what you're doing?

1031
01:20:20,397 --> 01:20:22,274
我相信我知道，威妮弗蕾德
I believe I do, Winifred.

1032
01:20:22,524 --> 01:20:26,111
一家英国银行运作于准确无误的基础之上
A British bank is run with precision

1033
01:20:26,361 --> 01:20:29,990
一个英国家庭也要运作与丝毫不差的基础上
A British home requires nothing less

1034
01:20:30,240 --> 01:20:34,286
传统，纪律和规则是我们必须的工具
Tradition, discipline and rules must be the tools

1035
01:20:34,536 --> 01:20:37,581
没有了它们，混乱，无序……
Without them disorder, chaos

1036
01:20:37,831 --> 01:20:39,708
道德崩溃
Moral disintegration

1037
01:20:39,958 --> 01:20:43,462
总之，带来的是可怕的，混乱不堪的局面
我非常赞同
In short you have a ghastly mess
I quite agree.

1038
01:20:43,712 --> 01:20:47,340
孩子们必须被引导，塑造和教导
The children must be moulded shaped and taught

1039
01:20:47,591 --> 01:20:50,844
生活是一场终究要面对和参与的战斗
That life's a looming battle to be faced and fought

1040
01:20:51,094 --> 01:20:53,680
总之，我很惊讶地听到我的孩子们讨论……
In short, I am disturbed to hear my children talking about...

1041
01:20:53,930 --> 01:20:55,557
跑到马路上的粉笔画里……
popping in and out of chalk pavement pictures...

1042
01:20:55,807 --> 01:20:58,977
与驯马师联欢，猎狐
consorting with racehorse persons, fox hunting.

1043
01:20:59,227 --> 01:21:01,271
当然，这件事本身我并不反对
Yes, well I don't mind that quite so much.

1044
01:21:01,521 --> 01:21:02,939
毕竟，它是传统的活动
At any rate, it's traditional.

1045
01:21:03,189 --> 01:21:05,525
但是，在天花板上的茶会，请问是怎么回事？
But tea parties on the ceiling? I ask you.

1046
01:21:05,775 --> 01:21:10,488
在天花板上开茶会，以及其它各种令人疑惑的出游！
Having tea parties on the ceiling and highly-questionable
outings of every other kind!

1047
01:21:10,739 --> 01:21:14,868
如果他们必须出游的话，那么，出游应该有
If they must go on outings These outings ought to be

1048
01:21:15,118 --> 01:21:17,871
明确的目标和……是的，实际意义
Fraught with purpose Yes, and practicality

1049
01:21:18,121 --> 01:21:19,706
还有那些愚蠢的话
These silly words like

1050
01:21:19,956 --> 01:21:23,209
比如超……超级……
Superca... Super...

1051
01:21:23,460 --> 01:21:26,588
超级霹……
超级霹雳快乐得不得了
Superca...
Supercalifragilistic-expialidocious.

1052
01:21:26,838 --> 01:21:28,339
是的，很好，就是你说的
Yes, well done. You said it.

1053
01:21:28,590 --> 01:21:30,759
到画里面
And popping through pictures

1054
01:21:31,009 --> 01:21:34,679
毫无疑义，没有任何必要
Have little use fulfil no basic need

1055
01:21:34,929 --> 01:21:37,140
他们需要开始认识真正的现实
They've got to learn the honest truth

1056
01:21:37,390 --> 01:21:39,517
尽管年纪还小，他们必须学会……
Despite their youth They must learn

1057
01:21:39,768 --> 01:21:43,480
向您那样的生活
正是如此
About the life you lead
Exactly.

1058
01:21:43,730 --> 01:21:48,735
他们需要体会统计分类帐差额簿的兴奋
They must feel the thrill of totting up a balanced book

1059
01:21:48,985 --> 01:21:52,947
成千个数字整齐地排成一行
很对
A thousand ciphers neatly in a row
Quite right.

1060
01:21:53,198 --> 01:21:56,826
当瞥一眼显示利润上升的图标
When gazing at a graph that shows the profits up

1061
01:21:57,076 --> 01:22:01,206
兴奋就溢满他们那小小的心灵
的确如此
Their little cup of joy should overflow
Precisely!

1062
01:22:01,456 --> 01:22:05,752
他们应该学着沿着你的脚印走路
是的
It's time they learned to walk in your footsteps
My footsteps.

1063
01:22:06,002 --> 01:22:09,672
满怀骄傲地沿着你的笔直且狭窄的道路前进
带着骄傲
To tread your straight and narrow path with pride
With pride.

1064
01:22:09,923 --> 01:22:13,718
明天，正如你所建议的那样
Tomorrow just as you suggest
Pressed and dressed

1065
01:22:13,968 --> 01:22:17,347
简和迈克尔将会穿着整齐地和你一起
Jane and Michael will be at your side

1066
01:22:17,597 --> 01:22:20,183
好极了，你说的准确无误……
Splendid! You hit the nail right on the...

1067
01:22:20,433 --> 01:22:22,769
和我一起？去哪儿？
At my side? Where are we going?

1068
01:22:23,019 --> 01:22:24,771
当然是去银行，完全按照您的建议
To the bank, of course, exactly as you proposed.

1069
01:22:25,021 --> 01:22:26,939
我的建议？
当然
I proposed?
Of course.

1070
01:22:27,190 --> 01:22:29,609
现在，如果你不介意，明天对于孩子们来讲是个重要的日子
Now, if you'll excuse me. Tomorrow's an important day for the children.

1071
01:22:29,859 --> 01:22:35,031
我要让他们睡个好觉，晚安
I shall see they have a proper night's sleep. Good night.

1072
01:22:44,040 --> 01:22:47,627
威妮弗蕾德，我说过要带孩子们去银行吗？
Winifred, did I say that I was going to take the children to the bank?

1073
01:22:47,877 --> 01:22:50,630
听上去确实是的，亲爱的
哦
It certainly sounded that way, dear.
Oh.

1074
01:22:50,880 --> 01:22:52,965
为什么不呢？一个极好的主意！
And why not? A capital idea!

1075
01:22:53,216 --> 01:22:56,219
这正是对付眼下混乱局面的一剂良药
Just the medicine they need for all this slipshod, sugary...

1076
01:22:56,469 --> 01:22:58,638
他们在这里接触的都是女人的不切实际的想法
female thinking they get around here all day long.

1077
01:22:58,888 --> 01:23:00,473
好主意，非常好
Quite right. Good idea. Quite right.

1078
01:23:00,723 --> 01:23:04,560
好主意，非常好
Good idea. Quite right.

1079
01:23:04,852 --> 01:23:07,563
玛丽?泼平斯，我们不让你走
Mary Poppins, we won't let you go!

1080
01:23:07,813 --> 01:23:09,649
走？你们到底在说什么？
Go? What on earth are you talking about?

1081
01:23:09,899 --> 01:23:14,153
你不是被解雇了吗？
解雇？当然没有！我从来没有被解雇过！
Didn't you get sacked?
Sacked? Certainly not!I am never sacked!

1082
01:23:14,403 --> 01:23:17,031
哦，玛丽?泼平斯！
好噢，好噢
Oh, Mary Poppins!
Hurrah, hurray, hurray,

1083
01:23:17,281 --> 01:23:19,659
我也不是五朔节花柱，请别围着我转。
hurray, hurray, hurray...
Neither am I a maypole. Kindly stop spinning about me.

1084
01:23:19,909 --> 01:23:22,828
但
但什么但……
But?
Goats butt, birds fly...

1085
01:23:23,079 --> 01:23:25,998
孩子们，你们必须早点睡觉，明天要跟你们的父亲一起出去
and children who are going on an outing with their father must get some sleep.

1086
01:23:26,248 --> 01:23:28,167
别这样，求求你
跟父亲出去？
Come along, please.
An outing with Father?

1087
01:23:28,417 --> 01:23:30,211
是的
我不信
Yes.
I don't believe it.

1088
01:23:30,461 --> 01:23:35,424
他以前从来没有带我们出去过
他从来没有带我们去任何地方
He's never taken us on an outing before.
He's never taken us anywhere.

1089
01:23:35,674 --> 01:23:37,259
你怎么做到的？
做到什么？
However did you manage it?
Manage what?

1090
01:23:37,510 --> 01:23:40,012
你一定用了什么方式把这主意塞到他的脑瓜里了
You must've put the idea in his head somehow.

1091
01:23:40,262 --> 01:23:42,431
胡说！
What an impertinent thing to say!

1092
01:23:42,681 --> 01:23:45,184
我怎么可能把主意塞进人们的脑袋里？真是的！
Me putting ideas into people's heads? Really!

1093
01:23:45,434 --> 01:23:47,728
他要带我们去哪里？
去银行
Where's he taking us?
To the bank.

1094
